# Error Taxonomy, Propagation, Retries & Timeouts

Define domain error classes, wrap third-party errors at boundaries, and retry only transient failures with capped backoff + jitter.

**Justification:** Clear error semantics and disciplined retries improve resilience and reduce noisy failures.

## Domain Error Types

Wrap third-party errors once at module boundaries; rethrow as domain errors.

```typescript
export class TransientNetworkError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string, cause?: unknown) {
    super(message); this.name = 'TransientNetworkError'; (this as any).cause = cause;
  }
}
```

## Retries & Timeouts

- Use capped exponential backoff with jitter for network calls
- Never retry non-idempotent operations
- Apply request timeouts and circuit breakers for unstable deps

